Line 1. Enter your nondeductible contributions to traditional I RAs for 2013, including those made for 2013 from January 1, 2014, through April 15, 2014 (see instructions). Dollars.
Line  2. Enter your total basis in traditional I R As (see instructions). Dollars.
Line  3. Add lines 1 and 2. Dollars.
Line 4. Enter those contributions included on line 1 that were made from January 1, 2014, through April 15, 2014. Dollars.
Line  5. Subtract line 4 from line 3. Dollars.
Line 6. Enter the value of all your traditional, SEP, and SIMPLE IRAs as of December 31, 2013, plus any outstanding rollovers. (see instructions). Dollars.

Line 7. Enter your distributions from traditional, SEP, and SIMPLE IRAs in 2013. Do not include rollovers, qualified charitable distributions, a one-time distribution to fund an HSA, conversions to a Roth IRA, certain returned contributions, or recharacterizations of traditional IRA contributions (see instructions). Dollars.

Line 8. Enter the net amount you converted from traditional, SEP, and SIMPLE IRAs to Roth I R As in 2013. Do not include amounts converted that you later recharacterized (see instructions). Also enter this amount on line 16. Dollars.
Line 9. Add lines 6, 7, and 8. Dollars.
Line 10. Divide line 5 by line 9. Enter the result as a decimal rounded to at least 3 places. If the result is 1.000 or more, enter “1.000”. Enter number before the decimal.
Line  11. Multiply line 8 by line 10. This is the nontaxable portion of the amount you converted to Roth I R As. Also enter this amount on line 17. Dollars.
Line 12. Multiply line 7 by line 10. This is the nontaxable portion of your distributions that you did not convert to a Roth I R A. Dollars.
Line 13. Add lines 11 and 12. This is the nontaxable portion of all your distributions. Dollars.
Line 14. Subtract line 13 from line 3. This is your total basis in traditional IRAs for 2013 and earlier years. Dollars.
Line 15. Taxable amount. Subtract line 12 from line 7. If more than zero, also include this amount on Form 1040, line 15b; Form 1040 A, line 11b; or Form 1040N R, line 16b. Dollars.

Line 16. If you completed Part I, enter the amount from line 8. Otherwise, enter the net amount you converted from traditional, SEP, and SIMPLE IRAs to Roth IRAs in 2013. Do not include amounts  you later recharacterized back to traditional, SEP, or SIMPLE IRAs in 2013 or 2014 (see instructions).  Dollars.
Line 17. If you completed Part 1, enter the amount from line 11. Otherwise, enter your basis in the amount  on line 16 (see instructions). Dollars.
Line 17. If you completed Part 1, enter the amount from line 11. Otherwise, enter your basis in the amount  on line 16 (see instructions). Dollars.
Line 19.  Enter your total nonqualified distributions from Roth I R As in 2013, including any qualified first-time homebuyer distributions (see instructions). Dollars.
Line 20. Qualified first-time homebuyer expenses (see instructions). Do not enter more than $10,000. Dollars.
Line 21. Subtract line 20 from line 19. If zero or less, enter zero, and skip lines 22 through 25. Dollars.
Line 22. Enter your basis in Roth IRA contributions (see instructions). Dollars.
Line 23. Subtract line 22 from line 21. If zero or less, enter zero, and skip lines 24 and 25. If more than zero, you may be subject to an additional tax (see instructions). Dollars.
Line 24. Enter your basis in conversions from traditional, SEP, and SIMPLE IRAs and rollovers from qualified retirement plans to a Roth IRA (see instructions). Dollars.
Line 25. Taxable amount. Subtract line 24 from line 23. If more than zero, also include this amount on Form 1040, line 15b; Form 1040A, line 11b; or Form 1040N R, line 16b. Dollars.
